== Java Libraries
- [http://xstream.codehaus.org/ XStream] is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again
- [http://www.jfugue.org/ JFugue] is for programming music without the complexities of MIDI
- [http://code.google.com/p/google-gson/ Gson] is used to convert Java Objects into their JSON representation
- [http://code.google.com/p/guava-libraries/ The Guava project] (from Google) contains collections, caching, primitives support, concurrency libraries, common annotations, string processing, I/O, and so forth
- [http://jsoup.org/ jsoup] is for working with real-world HTML
- [http://jcaptcha.sourceforge.net/ JCAPTCHA] is for captcha definition and integration
- [http://pdfbox.apache.org/ The Apache PDFBoxâ„¢ library] is for working with PDF documents
- [http://poi.apache.org/ Apache POI] is the Java API for Microsoft Documents
- [http://nekohtml.sourceforge.net/ NekoHTML] is a simple HTML scanner and tag balancer
- [http://code.google.com/p/daisydiff/ Daisy Diff] diffs (compares) HTML files
- [http://commons.apache.org/fileupload/ The Commons FileUpload package] makes it easy to add file upload capability
- [http://cssparser.sourceforge.net/ The CSS Parser] inputs CSS source and outputs a DOM tree
- [http://commons.apache.org/beanutils/ Apache Commons BeanUtils] provides wrappers around reflection and introspection capabilities
- [http://commons.apache.org/bsf/ Bean Scripting Framework] provides scripting language support and access to Java objects and methods from scripting languages
- [http://xmlgraphics.apache.org/batik/ Batik] is a toolkit for display, generation and manipulation of SVG images
- [http://quartz-scheduler.org/ Quartz] is a full-featured job scheduling service for any Java EE/SE application

